<item>
            <title>[LU-11475] LNet discovery: allow deleting primary_nid in router case</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-11475</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If the router responds with a ping or a push in which the primary_nid has been changed then allow the peer_ni to be changed as well. For non-router nodes, we can not remove the peer_ni because doing so will break the upper layers who rely on the primary_nid. Routers on the other hand are invisible to the upper layers. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
